03/12/2006
PRAGUE, Czech Republic -- The government has decided to open the local labour market to workers from Bulgaria and Romania after the two countries' accession to the EU next January. 
Prime Minister Marek Topolanek explained on Friday (December 1st) that while Prague does not want to impose restrictions, the government is prepared to protect the labour market, if necessary. 
(Darik, BNT - 01/12/06)
